subSubSection.paragraph:
The shells of
Parthenina varia
from Brazil (
Figs. 36–43
) are very similar to the illustration and description in
Odé ( 1993 c: 23 , figure on page 30 )
. There is great intraspecific variation in the rectilinearity of the whorls (
Figs. 36−39
), with some shells being more convex in profile (
Fig. 39
); in the expression of the axial ribs on the base, with some shells having strong axials (
Figs. 38−39
) while others have evanescent (
Fig. 37
) or almost absent axials (
Fig. 36
); and also in the strength of the spiral grooves, which are sometimes especially distinct on the base (
Figs. 42−43
).
